-- U.S. Helium Price Advanced 6.2 Percent in 2012, Government Says
-- B y   J a c o b   A d e l m a n
-- 2013-01-30T01:31:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-30/u-s-helium-price-advanced-6-2-percent-in-2012-government-says.html
The estimated price paid by private
buyers for U.S.-produced  helium  rose 6.2 percent in the year
ended September 2012, according to the U.S. Geological Survey.  Private businesses paid about $6.13 a cubic meter ($170 per
thousand cubic feet), the USGS said on its website, up from
$5.77 a cubic meter in the previous period. U.S. helium output
rose 5.6 percent to 75 million cubic meters from the previous
year, the USGS said. World helium output increased 0.6 percent
to 173 million cubic meters.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jacob Adelman in Tokyo at 
